FBIS4-37458 "drnes119_l_94005" FBIS-NES-94-119 Daily Report 21 Jun 1994 ISRAEL Rabin, Peres To End Contacts With 'Arafat Adviser Rabin, Peres To End Contacts With 'Arafat Adviser TA2106110694 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1000 GMT 21 Jun 94 TA2106110694 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el Hebrew BFN [Text] Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin and Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres have instructed their bureau officials and aides to cease all working contacts with Dr. Ahmad al-Tibi, who is described as PLO Chairman Yasir 'Arafat's adviser. The instructions came in the wake of a legal opinion regarding al-Tibi's status as an Israeli citizen. This was reported by our political correspondent Shlomo Raz.
